<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hilding" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hilding</orth> (from the Saxon healdan; one who is held or kept) a base, menial wretch; used of both sexes: <bibl n="shak. shr 2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.6.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Alls III, 6, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.4.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 4, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.169" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 169</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.3.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 3, 128</bibl>. Adjectively: <cit><quote>some h. fellow,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.57" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 57</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a h. foe,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.2.29" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 2, 29</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>